Description:
Use iverilog -S -g2012 to compile the following:
module test(input clk, input rst, input a, output reg [1:0] state);
    reg [1:0] next_state;
    reg [3:0] pos;
    reg [3:0] next_pos;

    always @(*) begin
        next_state = state;
       if(a) begin
           next_state = '0;
       end
    end
    always @(posedge clk, posedge rst) begin
        if(rst) begin
            state <= '1;
            // pos <= '0;
        end else begin
            state <= next_state;
            pos <= next_pos;
        end
    end
endmodule


Gives message sorry: Not all bits of 'state' are asynchronously set or reset. This is not currently supported in synthesis.
Turns out it's actually because of pos, not state. uncommenting the line that sets pos to 0s gets rid of the error message.
